  "local_port": 50020,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "My viber on PC doesnt connect to internet. whats the problem? It shows me the messages that other send me but I cant reply through my pc.",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear you're experiencing issues with Viber on your PC. While you can see messages sent by others, being unable to send replies typically indicates a connection or configuration problem. Here's a comprehensive guide to help you troubleshoot and resolve this issue:\n\n### 1. **Verify Your Internet Connection**\n\n- **Confirm Connectivity:**\n  - **Web Browsing:** Open a web browser and visit several websites to ensure your internet connection is stable.\n  - **Other Apps:** Check if other internet-dependent applications (e.g., email, streaming services) are functioning correctly.\n\n- **Restart Network Devices:**\n  - **Modem/Router:** Unplug your modem and router, wait for about 30 seconds, then plug them back in. This can resolve temporary connectivity issues.\n\n### 2. **Restart Viber on Your PC**\n\n- **Fully Close Viber:**\n  - **Windows:** Right-click the Viber icon in the system tray and select \"Quit Viber.\"\n  - **Mac:** Right-click the Viber icon in the dock and select \"Quit.\"\n\n- **Reopen Viber:**\n  - Launch Viber again and attempt to send a message.\n\n### 3. **Ensure Viber Is Updated**\n\n- **Check for Updates:**\n  - **Windows:**\n    - Open Viber, click on the three horizontal lines (Menu) in the top-left corner.\n    - Navigate to **Settings > Help & Feedback > Check for Updates**.\n  - **Mac:**\n    - Open Viber, go to **Viber > Check for Updates** in the menu bar.\n\n- **Update if Necessary:** Follow on-screen instructions to update to the latest version.\n\n### 4. **Check Firewall and Antivirus Settings**\n\nSometimes, security software can block Viber's ability to send messages.\n\n- **Windows Firewall:**\n  1. Press `Win + R`, type `control`, and press Enter to open the Control Panel.\n  2. Go to **System and Security > Windows Defender Firewall > Allow an app or feature through Windows Defender Firewall**.\n  3. Ensure **Viber** is listed and both **Private** and **Public** boxes are checked.\n  4. If Viber isn\u2019t listed, click **Allow another app**, browse to Viber\u2019s installation folder, select `Viber.exe`, and add it.\n\n- **Third-Party Antivirus:**\n  - Open your antivirus software and check the list of blocked applications.\n  - If Viber is blocked, whitelist it or adjust the settings to allow Viber's network access.\n\n### 5. **Check Proxy and VPN Settings**\n\n- **Disable VPN:**\n  - If you're using a VPN, try disconnecting it to see if Viber works without it.\n\n- **Check Proxy Settings:**\n  - **Windows:**\n    1. Go to **Settings > Network & Internet > Proxy**.\n    2. Ensure that no unwanted proxy is enabled. If you're unsure, you can disable \"Use a proxy server.\"\n  - **Mac:**\n    1. Open **System Preferences > Network**.\n    2. Select your network connection and click **Advanced**.\n    3. Navigate to the **Proxies** tab and ensure no unintended proxies are selected.\n\n### 6. **Re-login to Viber**\n\n- **Log Out and Log Back In:**\n  1. Open Viber on your PC.\n  2. Go to **Settings > Account**.\n  3. Select **Log Out**.\n  4. Close Viber completely, reopen it, and log back in by scanning the QR code with your mobile device.\n\n### 7. **Reinstall Viber**\n\nIf the above steps don't work, reinstalling Viber might resolve corrupted files or settings issues.\n\n- **Uninstall Viber:**\n  - **Windows:**\n    1. Press `Win + I` to open Settings.\n    2. Go to **Apps > Apps & features**.\n    3. Find **Viber**, click on it, and select **Uninstall**.\n  - **Mac:**\n    1. Open **Finder**.\n    2. Go to **Applications**.\n    3. Drag **Viber** to the Trash.\n\n- **Download the Latest Version:**\n  - Visit the [official Viber download page](https://www.viber.com/en/download/) and download the latest version for your operating system.\n\n- **Install Viber:**\n  - Run the installer and follow the on-screen instructions.\n  - After installation, log in by scanning the QR code with your mobile device.\n\n### 8. **Check Viber Server Status**\n\nOccasionally, Viber might experience server outages or issues that affect messaging functionality.\n\n- **Official Channels:**\n  - Check [Viber\u2019s official Twitter account](https://twitter.com/viber) or [Viber\u2019s official website](https://www.viber.com/en/) for any announcements regarding outages.\n\n- **Downdetector:**\n  - Visit [Downdetector\u2019s Viber page](https://downdetector.com/status/viber/) to see if other users are reporting similar issues.\n\n### 9. **Ensure Your Mobile Device Has Internet Access**\n\nViber on PC often syncs with your mobile device. Make sure your phone has a stable internet connection:\n\n- **Check Connectivity:**\n  - Ensure your phone is connected to the internet via Wi-Fi or mobile data.\n\n- **Restart Viber on Mobile:**\n  - Close and reopen the Viber app on your phone to ensure it's functioning correctly.\n\n### 10. **Contact Viber Support**\n\nIf none of the above solutions work, reaching out to Viber\u2019s support team might be necessary.\n\n- **Submit a Support Request:**\n  - Visit the [Viber Help Center](https://help.viber.com/) and navigate to the support or contact section.\n  - Provide detailed information about your issue, including your operating system, Viber version, and the troubleshooting steps you've already taken.\n\n### Summary\n\nBy systematically following these troubleshooting steps, you should be able to identify and resolve the issue preventing you from replying to messages on Viber for PC. Start with verifying your internet connection and checking software updates, then move on to more specific settings like firewalls and proxies. Reinstalling the application or contacting support are effective final steps if the problem persists.\n\nIf you have any further questions or need additional assistance, feel free to ask!",
